                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>104900</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-66162"><name nymRef="#Χαρίτιμος"><supplied reason="lost">Χαρ</supplied>ίτιμον</name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64701"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Κλητόμαχος">Κλητο<supplied reason="lost">μάχω</supplied></name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64705"><name nymRef="#Κλητόμαχος"><supplied reason="lost">Κλ</supplied><unclear>η</unclear>τόμ<supplied reason="lost">α</supplied>χος</name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-66162"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Χαρίτιμος">Χαριτ<supplied reason="lost">ίμω</supplied></name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="3"/><space quantity="6" unit="character"/> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι"><supplied reason="lost">ἀνέ</supplied><unclear>θη</unclear><supplied reason="lost">κε</supplied></w>
                            <supplied reason="lost"><space quantity="7" unit="character"/></supplied>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="2">
                        <lem resp="#SECir #cdl2003a">Χαριτ<supplied reason="lost">ίμω</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SEG">Χαροτ<supplied reason="lost">ίμω</supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="3">
                        <lem resp="#cdl2003a"><supplied reason="lost">ἀνέ</supplied><unclear>θη</unclear><supplied reason="lost">κε</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig><unclear>ρ</unclear></orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Statue de</supplied> Kharitimos fils de Klètomakhos consacrée par Klètomakhos fils de Kharitimos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Statue of</supplied> Charitimos son of Kletomachos dedicated by Kletomachos son of Charitimos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Statua di</supplied> Charitimos figlio di Kletomachos dedicata da Kletomachos figlio di Charitimos.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The date and spot of find are indicated from the sketchbook of Oliverio, who had found two out of three fragments. The three of them
                are now in the Museum, where Morelli observed and published them, unfortunately without photograph.</p>
	<p>The dedicant, who is most probably the son of the man honoured by a statue, might also be a man who subscribed ca. 280 BC (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr065210</ref>, i.151).</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
